What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?

git sets up hidden files and preps the directory to be a repository
you need to do an initial commit.

How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository? What value do you think it offers?

the staging area is a temporary place to start changes to your respository. the value is you can reason out what changes you are going to make and see them before you actually make them.
